An investigation by Buffalo City Metro into a KwaZulu-Natal-based company that demanded an increase of R26.6-million to complete a water and sanitation project has opened a can of worms. Metro officials have been accused of colluding with the company in the controversial tender for a Mdantsane community.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions